commentary: Kumar to Kieswetter, OUT edged, and gone! Praveen has struck with the new ball. He zinged one down on a full length and got the ball to seam away from Kieswetter, who fished at it away from his body and sent a clear edge through to Dhoni. India will be mightily pleased with this early strike, which will stall England's hopes of attacking the new ball

commentary: Yadav to Swann, no run a big swing and a miss! This definitely kept low. Swann had stayed deep in the crease and tried to heave across the line to midwicket, but the ball zipped right under the bat

commentary: Yadav to Swann, OUT undone by the low bounce! He should've been on his guard after that last delivery. Yadav moved his line a little straighter but again Swann swished across the line, again a low, scuttling delivery buzzed under his bat, but this time it clattered into the stumps. Swann has an accusatory look at the pitch as he walks off, but that's not the first one to have kept low today

commentary: Yadav to Patel, OUT well, that was unnecessary. The last shot was classy, this one was just atrocious. He knows the ball is keeping low, but he swings merrily across the line at a straight length delivery, and is cleaned up. And that's about it for England. Dernbach comes out to face the music, and this shouldn't take long
